<head>RISK</head><list type="altnames">
<item>CHANCE</item>
<item>UNCERTAINTY</item>
<item>UNPREDICTABILITY</item>
<item>PRECARIOUSNESS</item>
<item>INSTABILITY</item>
<item>INSECURITY</item>
<item>PERILOUSNESS</item>
<item>RISKINESS</item></list><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">冒</item></list>
<div type="definition">
<p>ACT so as to DELIBERATELY CAUSE ONESELF or one's PROPERTY to be in DANGER.</p></div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>冒險 is the standard word for taking a risk.</p>
<p>保險額 refers to the quantified risk.</p>
<p>作賭注 is to risk money in gambling.</p>
<p>冒危險去做 is to take a risk and go ahead with an action.</p>
<p>風險 refers to a hazard or risk involved in an action.</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p></div></div>
